    "narrative": "The Austin Waves head into today\u2019s slate leaning heavily on **Luis Robert Jr.** (76.49) and **Kyle Tucker** (74.75), our two highest-rated starters. **Luis Robert Jr.** benefits from a high-upside matchup against Jose Quintana, with his score buoyed significantly by a +14% dynamic platoon advantage and a favorable spot in the batting order. Meanwhile, **Kyle Tucker** remains an elite play despite facing Shota Imanaga; the combination of a +9% SP skill advantage and beneficial wind conditions keeps his floor exceptionally high. **Jackson Merrill** (68.06) and **Josh Lowe** (66.42) are also locked in as strong starters, with both players drawing favorable platoon matchups against right-handed arms that push their expected production well into the \"Strong\" tier.\n\nThe primary point of friction in today\u2019s optimization was the exclusion of **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.**, who finished at 51.36. While he holds a strong base projection, he ultimately fell short of the starting rotation due to an unfavorable dynamic platoon split against the left-handed Bryan Hudson and a poor expected lineup position (#8), which hampered his projected R and RBI potential compared to the utility floor offered by **Nolan Schanuel**. We are closely monitoring the 45% rain risk surrounding **Josh Lowe** and **Nolan Schanuel** at the Seth Lugo matchup; if the weather forces a postponement, we are prepared to pivot to the bench, where **Marcell Ozuna** offers the most reliable secondary upside. Additionally, with lineup spots for **Nasim Nunez**, **Gunnar Henderson**, **Jacob Wilson**, and **Brady House** still pending, we advise vigilance. **Gunnar Henderson** faces a notably tough test against the 2.34 xERA of Connelly Early, and while his base projection is elite, the SP difficulty creates a volatility window that we are watching closely as official lineups drop.",
